# Cursor Prompt — Full Platform Rebrand (Industrial Modern, Operator-Focused)

You are rebranding the entire FieldCrew platform UI.

IMPORTANT:
- Do NOT change navigation structure or feature layout.
- This is a visual system overhaul only.
- Apply consistently across ALL pages.
- Remove generic SaaS aesthetic.
- Implement a rugged, operator-focused design system.

Brand Direction:
- Industrial Modern
- Deep Navy + Burnt Orange
- Strong numeric emphasis
- No fluff
- No pastel tones
- No playful design

---

# 1) Global Theme System

Update theme tokens:

Primary Background:
Deep navy for sidebar (#0F172A range)

Surface:
Soft off-white (#F8FAFC or similar)

Accent:
Burnt orange (#F97316 range)

Neutral:
Steel greys (#334155 / #64748B)

Danger:
Muted red (#DC2626 range)

Remove:
- Purple accents
- Random blues
- Pastel warning backgrounds

---

# 2) Typography

Increase hierarchy:

Page Title:
Bold, strong

KPI Numbers:
Very large, heavy weight

Labels:
Small, uppercase optional

Reduce softness.
Increase numeric dominance.

---

# 3) Card Styling

Refactor Card component:

- Slightly reduce border radius (less soft)
- Remove heavy borders
- Use subtle shadow
- Introduce accent left stripe option for highlighted cards

Variants:
- Default
- Warning (subtle orange tint)
- Critical (subtle red tint)
- Highlight (dark navy background + orange accent)

---

# 4) Buttons

Primary:
Burnt orange background
Dark navy text or white (test contrast)

Secondary:
Outlined navy

No soft gradients.
No pastel backgrounds.

Add subtle hover elevation.

---

# 5) Charts

Create shared chart theme:

- Thicker lines (2–3px)
- Burnt orange primary line
- Navy secondary
- Darker gridlines
- Reduced clutter
- No pastel fills

Charts must feel deliberate and controlled.

---

# 6) Sidebar

Keep dark navy.
Active state:
Burnt orange accent bar on left.

Typography slightly heavier.
No excessive hover animations.

---

# 7) Recoverable Profit Card

Redesign to be signature element:

- Dark navy background
- Burnt orange accent
- Large dollar figure
- Clear subtext
- No gradient softness
- Strong and confident

---

# 8) Microcopy Adjustments

Replace friendly language with operational tone:

- "Weekly margin overview"
- "Overtime cost (current week)"
- "Jobs exceeding estimate"
- "Revenue per labour hour"

Remove conversational fluff.

---

# 9) Consistency Pass

Apply across:
- Dashboard
- Reporting
- Jobs
- Workers
- Timesheets
- Payroll
- Settings
- Clock in/out

Ensure:
- Same radius
- Same spacing
- Same accent usage
- Same typography scale

---

# 10) Acceptance Criteria

Platform feels:
- Rugged
- Operator-focused
- Recognisable
- Confident
- No-nonsense

It should no longer resemble:
Generic AI SaaS dashboard.

Begin implementation by:
1) Updating theme tokens
2) Refactoring Card/Button/Badge
3) Updating chart styling
4) Applying visual system across pages
